  "blocks": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "How to proceed with auto air conditioner failure diagnosis"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The self-diagnostic function of the auto A/C control unit can also check DTCs."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Turn ignition OFF (LOCK) mode."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "",
      "text": "2. Connect HDS to the data link coupler (A)."
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "1366_3.0_jpn_11266161_2.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "3",
      "text": "Turn ignition to ON mode"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "4",
      "text": "Verify that HDS communicates with the vehicle and the auto A/C control unit. If it does not communicate, Inspect the data link circuitry.",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "T002567",
          "label": "Inspect the data link circuitry.",
          "resolved": false
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "5",
      "text": "Select Body Electrical -> Auto A/C -> DTC in HDS."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "6",
      "text": "Check DTC."
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        {
          "text": "For information on the use of HDS, refer to the HDS instruction manual."
        },
        {
          "text": "After repairing the faulty part, clear the DTC with HDS."
        },
        {
          "text": "When clearing DTC, work according to HDS instructions."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Turn ignition OFF (LOCK) mode."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "",
      "text": "2. Connect HDS to the data link coupler (A)."
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "1366_3.0_jpn_11266162_2.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "3",
      "text": "Turn ignition to ON mode"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "4",
      "text": "Verify that HDS communicates with the vehicle and the auto A/C control unit. If it does not communicate, Inspect the data link circuitry.",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "T002567",
          "label": "Inspect the data link circuitry.",
          "resolved": false
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "5",
      "text": "Execute Body Electrical -> Auto A/C -> Inspect -> Auto A/C Self-Check in HDS."
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        {
          "text": "For information on the use of HDS, refer to the HDS instruction manual."
        },
        {
          "text": "After repairing the faulty part, clear the DTC with HDS."
        },
        {
          "text": "When clearing DTC, work according to HDS instructions."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The auto A/C control unit has a self-diagnostic function."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Turn ignition OFF (LOCK) mode and then ON mode."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "2",
      "text": "Press and hold the ON/OFF switch, then press the rear defroster/mirror heater switch five times within 10 seconds. All LCD segments light up for 2 seconds, and immediately after that, self-diagnosis begins."
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        {
          "text": "The self-diagnostic operation is valid only once after the ignition ON mode."
        },
        {
          "text": "During self-diagnosis, all systems are automatically activated for up to approximately 90 seconds."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "",
      "text": "3. After self-diagnosis is completed, if there is an error, the error code corresponding to the faulty part of the temperature setting indicator ''88'' lights up. After the error code is lit for 1 second, it is turned off for 0.5 seconds, after which the error code is lit repeatedly. If there is more than one failure, the error codes are turned on in order of error code (from 01 to number), and after all error codes are turned on, the display returns to the first error code. If there is no abnormality, ''no'' lights up."
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "1366_3.0_jpn_11038192_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "4",
      "text": "During the self-diagnostic function, normal operation is restored by pressing any switch (except the A/C switch) or by putting the ignition OFF (LOCK) mode."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Turn ignition OFF (LOCK) mode and then ON mode."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "2",
      "text": "Press and hold the AUTO switch, then press and hold the ON/OFF switch. While keeping both switches pressed, the failure code history is displayed."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "",
      "text": "3. If there has been an abnormality in the past, the error code corresponding to the faulty part of the set temperature indicator ''88'' will light up. The error code is illuminated for 1 second, followed by 0.5 seconds of the light being off, after which the error code is illuminated repeatedly. If there is more than one failure, the error codes are turned on in order of error code (from 01 to number), and after all error codes are turned on, the display returns to the first error code. If there is no abnormality, ''no'' lights up."
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "1366_3.0_jpn_11038193_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "4",
      "text": "Ignition OFF (LOCK) mode to return to normal operation."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Turn ignition OFF (LOCK) mode."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "2",
      "text": "Press the AUTO switch and the front defroster switch simultaneously, and while holding them down, place the ignition in the ON mode. Holding both switches down for 5 seconds clears the history, and the front defroster indicator flashes while both switches are held down."
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "3",
      "text": "Check the failure code history again to see if any failure history points remain."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "After repairing the faulty part, the presence of the faulty part shall be checked again by the self-diagnostic function."
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "1366_3.0_jpn_11038194_3.0_disp.png"
    },
